              "free_text": [
                " The electrostatic tandem accelerator",
                "               UKP-2-1."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-resolution HpGe detector ORTEC GEM2P of",
                "volume 111 cm3.",
                "The absolute detector gamma-ray efficiency for",
                "E(g)=661-3253.6 keV was determined by using calibrated",
                "Cs-137, Co-60 and Co-56 sources with intensities known",
                "to better than 1%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC",
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "13-AL-27(P,G)14-SI-28,,DA",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "13-AL-27(P,G)14-SI-28,,DA",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "13-AL-27(P,G)14-SI-28",
                        "target": "13-AL-27",
                        "projectile": "P",
                        "process": "G",
                        "product": "14-SI-28",
                        "quantity": ",DA",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",DA"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The energy calibration of",
                "the accelerator was tested during the course of the",
                "experiment by the well-known resonances."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*. To minimize gamma-ray absorption and",
                "Compton scattering in the setup, the target chamber",
                "was made of stainless steel with a wall thickness of",
                " 1.5 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The targets were produced by evaporation of natural",
                "carbon onto 1.5 mm thick Cu backings. Six targets with",
                "thicknesses of 9.0+-0.6 and 11.0+-0.7 ug/cm2 for",
                "measurements at E(p)=354, 390, 460 and 463 keV,",
                "13.5+-0.4 and 23.5+-1.2 ug/cm2 for E(p)=565 and",
                "750 keV, 40+-2 and 48.0+-2.4 ug/cm2 for E(p)=1061 keV",
                "were used.",
                "By using different targets at the same energies E(p)",
                "it was found that the effective beam energies within",
                "all targets at the corresponding energies E(p)lab were",
                "well described by E(eff)=E(p)=E(p)lab-0.5*deltaE(p)"
              ]
            }
          ],
